WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.460
I want you all to think that for a minute you are living in New York City and you don't

00:00:06.460 --> 00:00:11.600
own a car, the subway is running late, Uber rides are too expensive, you can actually

00:00:11.600 --> 00:00:13.460
still hop onto a city bike.

00:00:14.220 --> 00:00:17.760
It's small, it's readily available, it gets you to your destination, it can drop it off.

00:00:17.820 --> 00:00:19.580
Just be careful when you're riding one in New York City.

00:00:20.400 --> 00:00:26.280
So that is how I would actually present some of the data on KTX1001 in heavily pre-treated

00:00:26.280 --> 00:00:27.700
relapsed refractory myeloma patients.

00:00:27.700 --> 00:00:33.340
So we know that 4-14 translocation is seen in about 10-15% of all new myeloma and some

00:00:33.340 --> 00:00:35.780
marker of high, more aggressive disease biology.

00:00:36.420 --> 00:00:41.120
And these patients with 4-14 translocation tend to have higher levels of MM-set expression

00:00:41.120 --> 00:00:45.620
that actually leads to epigenetic signaling and myeloma cell proliferation.

00:00:46.080 --> 00:00:50.380
And what essentially KTX does is that it actually binds to the MM-set, puts some brakes on the

00:00:50.380 --> 00:00:56.520
MM-set and actually decreases the levels of H3K36 molecules and then leads to downregulation

00:00:56.520 --> 00:00:57.520
of oncogenic signals.

00:00:57.700 --> 00:00:58.700
So it's a very interesting study.

00:00:58.700 --> 00:01:00.260
So we're going to go through the link.

00:01:00.260 --> 00:01:04.940
It has been explored for relapsed refractory myeloma in our phase one study.

00:01:04.940 --> 00:01:11.040
A total of 40 patients were enrolled in the study in nine different dosing cohorts.

00:01:11.040 --> 00:01:17.200
The inclusion criteria did require patients to have exposure to PI, IMIDs, and CD38 antibody,

00:01:17.200 --> 00:01:19.640
have measurable disease and adequate performance status.

00:01:19.640 --> 00:01:26.520
KTX was given as an oral agent without dexamethasone, given twice daily, again, and nine different

00:01:26.520 --> 00:01:27.580
dosing cohorts.

00:01:27.700 --> 00:01:34.040
And I would focus on this patient demographic slide here that you can see.

00:01:34.120 --> 00:01:40.300
40 patients were enrolled and 100% of them were triple-class refractory.

00:01:40.300 --> 00:01:47.520
In fact, 40% of them had a prior BCMA CAR-T, 60% of them had a prior BCMA bispecific or

00:01:47.520 --> 00:01:54.700
ADC, and another 40% of them, in fact, had a GPRC5D or FCRH5 Bispecific.

00:01:55.780 --> 00:01:57.620
Patient has a median of six prior lines of therapy.

00:01:57.700 --> 00:02:00.380
And 80% of them are in fact penta-exposed.

00:02:00.380 --> 00:02:06.820
414 translocation was in about 50% of the patient and remaining 25% either had deletion 17P or

00:02:06.820 --> 00:02:07.820
1q amplification.

00:02:07.820 --> 00:02:12.500
So truly, a heavily pre-treated relapsed refractory myeloma patient population that doesn't really

00:02:12.500 --> 00:02:16.480
have a lot of options left behind.

00:02:16.480 --> 00:02:22.460
Looking at the primary objective of the study, which is safety assessment, major dose limiting

00:02:22.460 --> 00:02:24.640
toxicity was thrombocytopenia.

00:02:24.640 --> 00:02:25.780
Grade three or higher events were seen in about 20% of the patients.

00:02:25.780 --> 00:02:26.780
Grade three or higher events were seen in about 20% of the patients.

00:02:26.780 --> 00:02:31.440
Grade three neutropenia or anemia is only in about 25% of the patients.

00:02:31.440 --> 00:02:35.680
So more impact on the platelet count and the hemoglobin and ANC.

00:02:35.680 --> 00:02:38.100
Very few cases of febrile neutropenia of only 5%.

00:02:38.100 --> 00:02:42.940
When you look at non-heme AEEs, you only see about 10% case of grade three fatigue and

00:02:42.940 --> 00:02:45.920
infections in these patients.

00:02:45.920 --> 00:02:50.000
And looking at the efficacy, again, remember, this is a heavily pre-treated patient population.

00:02:50.000 --> 00:02:54.500
We are looking at different dose levels and we are only giving it as a monotherapy without

00:02:54.500 --> 00:02:55.500
dexamethasone.

00:02:55.500 --> 00:03:00.360
And yet we are seeing responses of stable disease are better seen in about 40% of the

00:03:00.360 --> 00:03:01.360
patients.

00:03:01.360 --> 00:03:03.000
Many of these responses are stable disease.

00:03:03.000 --> 00:03:04.680
There were few partial responses as well.

00:03:04.680 --> 00:03:09.800
And one of the patients actually achieved a VGPR that lasted beyond 12 months.

00:03:09.800 --> 00:03:16.480
We did see that with the administration of KTX, there was a diminishing in the size or

00:03:16.480 --> 00:03:21.600
measurement of HTK86 in the peripheral blood, as well as in the bone marrow.

00:03:21.600 --> 00:03:25.460
And we did in fact see a decreased proliferation in the tumor, as well as increased proliferation

00:03:25.460 --> 00:03:27.800
in the immune cells.

00:03:27.800 --> 00:03:33.100
And here is actually one of my patients who was part of the presentation at ASH, a 60-year-old

00:03:33.100 --> 00:03:37.560
gentleman who got diagnosed with multiple myeloma in 2015, has been at MSK for a long

00:03:37.560 --> 00:03:42.300
period of time, had received at least two transplants, had received quadruple therapy

00:03:42.300 --> 00:03:49.840
as well, had BCMA bispecifics, CAR-T, GPRC, 5D therapy, in total 16 prior lines of therapy

00:03:49.840 --> 00:03:54.460
with extra medullary disease and rising free light chains at a time they got enrolled on

00:03:54.460 --> 00:03:55.460
the KTX.

00:03:55.460 --> 00:03:59.340
And even when the patient got started on KTX, they actually had an increase in the free

00:03:59.340 --> 00:04:00.340
light chains.

00:04:00.340 --> 00:04:04.060
But within a month's time, we started noticing that the light chains started trickling down,

00:04:04.060 --> 00:04:07.840
and eventually the patient achieved very good partial response that lasted beyond a year.

00:04:07.840 --> 00:04:10.640
Eventually, the patients succumbed to their disease with extra medullary disease, but

00:04:10.640 --> 00:04:16.580
we did notice any response to EMD as well, just with the monotherapy with KTX.

00:04:16.580 --> 00:04:21.680
So in conclusion, KTX is a selective inhibitor of MMSAT and NSD2.

00:04:21.680 --> 00:04:25.420
It has shown us tolerable safety profile, it has actually shown some efficacy in heavily

00:04:25.420 --> 00:04:29.900
predated myeloma patients, there are ongoing trials that are actually looking at combinations

00:04:29.900 --> 00:04:35.180
of KTX with carfilazomab as well as with cell mods like mezignamide.

00:04:35.180 --> 00:04:40.540
I do think in the era where we are using CAR-T and bispecifics in the frontline settings,

00:04:40.540 --> 00:04:45.600
the patients that are relapsed or refractory a few years from now are going to be refractory

00:04:45.600 --> 00:04:51.200
to a lot of the options that we have available right now in the form of CAR-T and bispecifics.

00:04:51.200 --> 00:04:55.300
So molecules like KTX would actually be an option for MMSAT.

00:04:55.300 --> 00:04:59.700
many of these patients especially when we are looking at targeted therapy as well thank you
